property.value:
Verification:
To perform verification, double-click on the MathematicalModel 
converter. On model type, select "Communicating Timed Automata", 
and set your target file with name in "*.d", e.g., DE_model.d.
The file itself is not difficult to understand, with detailed
comments mentioning indexes of processes.

Note that since since in timed automata, the number of states 
is finite, for TimedDelay actors abstraction must be performed
to set the buffer size. This can be tuned with the parameter.

In the following are some possible specification. Copy one 
line of the following to an empty file, and rename it as "*.risk".

/* Buffer overflow of the TimedDelay actor */
Buffer_Overflow[4];
/* Buffer overflow of the TimedDelay2 actor */
Buffer_Overflow[5];
/* The car light and the pedestrian light will not be green simultaneously */
CarLightNormal_State_Cgrn[1] && PedestrianLightNormal_State_Pgrn[2];
